already_interacted: ^Jupiter doesn't seem interested in talking to you.

c-0: ^ You probably know Earth more than me...
^Ah, right. Earth's only moon. I remember you now.

new: ^Oh? We don't get many visitors. Though, I'm not surprised you found your way to me.
^Jupiiiiie! You're not gonna bring in another moon, are you?

g-0: ^Oh no you don't! Jupiter's got enough moons to make them happy, thank you very much!

main: ^What are you doing so far from Earth? You lost or something?
^I got lost exploring the Asteroid Belt.

c-0: ^ I'm uhh... looking for a new planet.

lost: ^Shouldn't you be with Earth though? How'd you get split from them?
main2: ^Well, we can't help you there, hun. Jupiter's so good to us!
^Jupiter flexes and shows off their Great Red Spot. The surrounding moons swoon.

c-0: ^ I think it looks really nice on you.
^Thanks... uh, that's just how I roll.
^Ah, so tough! Jupiter really has it all!
^Except room for more moons, so back off!
c-1: ^Ah, so tough! Jupiter really has it all!
^Except room for more moons, so back off!
c-2: ^Oh yeah, Earth's probably pretty stormy as well... sorry.
^Ah, forget about Earth! That prick has nothing on our Jupiter!
^But our Jupiter has enough moons already, so back off!
g-0: ^Hey, how about you back off? It's not like they even notice you!
^How about you BOTH back off! I'm their favorite-- right Jupie?
^... you should probably leave. This can get ugly fast...

JupiterSecond: ^Oh, hey Moon. Wasn't sure if you would come back.
^Well, I liked talking to you earlier, and...
^I want to get to know you better.
^I want to talk to some of your other moons.
^I just wanted to hang out with you.

c-0: ^ ... uh, I wanted to get to know you better.
^Me? Well, I'm the largest and oldest planet around here. I wanted to be a start at one point, but that didn't work out.
^ You can just... be a star?
^It's pretty complicated, but you need a lot of mass to start fusion reactions. I was big, but not dense enough.
^And you should've seen then 4 billion years ago!
c-1: ^ So... what do you do now?
^Not much, really. I guess I chill with Saturn and watch the Asteroid Belt.
^Not much? What about all those big rocks you hurl around?
^ ... uh, I wanted to chat with... your other moons?
^You wanted to talk to me, Jupie?
^Actually, Moon wanted to talk to you.
^Hey, I wanna talk to Moon too! What's up?
^How do you feel about Jupiter as a planet?
^Do you always fight over Jupiter like that?

c-0: ^... you know, I am still here...
^Jupiter's great! They may not always tell us, but they love each and every one of us.
^I've never felt safer than with Jupiter at my barycenter.
c-1: ^ So are you... um... do you always...

c-2: ^ ... uh, I want to just, hang out?
^Yeah, sure thing. You can chill with me.
^Waaaait a minute. I know what THAT means. You're trying to fall into my orbit again!
^YOUR orbit? Who thinks YOU get to take over the orbit?
^Do you always fight over Jupiter like that?

c-0: ^ So are you... um... do you always...
c-1: ^Could you not fight right now? We have a guest, after all.

fight: ^What? Oh hun, I'm so sorry! You must think we hate each other!
^... OK, Europa hates everyone. But the rest of us... I don't know.
^I think we just riled up sometimes. Orbiting such a strong planet can do that to a moon.
main: ^Toughest in the solar system! That's our Jupie!
^Hm? Oh, it's nothing. Nothing you need to worry about, at least.

c-0: ^ ... y'know, you don't always have to be tough. It's ok to express your emotions sometimes.
c-1: ^ Okay... well, if you need anything, I'm here for you.
g-0: ^That's really nice of you to say...
^You suddenly notice that Jupiter is starting to cry. They try to hide it, but you can hear them choking back sobs.
^AH! What did you do to them?
^I-I don't know what happened! We were just talking, and-- and...

JupiterThird: ^Oh, Moon! I wasn't sure if you would be back.
^Yeah, you seemed even more shaken up than Jupie.
^Hey, guys, could you give us a bit of space? I want to talk to Moon for a bit.
^We'll be just within earshot if you need us!
^The moons retreat just far enough away so that they can still eavesdrop on your conversation.

c-1: ^Yeah, I'm feeling better. Thanks for asking.
c-2: ^You're probably wondering what... that... was all about. Well...
g-0: ^Last time you were here, you made me realize that I had been pushing back my feelings for a long time. I wanted to look tough for my moons because that was what they liked about me.
^But I guess that wasn't really what I liked about myself. I mean, sometimes it was alright, but... it's a lot of pressure sometimes.
^And the constant fighting doesn't help either.
^Yeah, that sounds awful. Unfortunately, I can relate to that.
^Oh, that's right, you split with Earth. If you don't mind talking about it, what happened between you two?

c-3: ^ A lot, over a long time. They were nice at first, but gradually, I felt ignored. They were always so self-centered, too busy with whatever was going on on their surface.

talk: ^I would get in the way of asteroids for them, and they never seemed to even notice. The one time they did was when I let one slip, and they got really mad and started yelling at me about all the dinosaurs I killed.

^And that might have been okay, but I could never get past those humans. I'd told Earth over and over to get rid of those humans before they got dangerous, but they just didn't listen-- even when some of those humans landed on my surface.
^Wait, the humans left Earth? Since when could they do that?
^Pretty recently. It's fine, I don't have any. They can't survive for long without Earth.
^But yeah, after that... I guess it finally hit me that Earth just didn't care about me. So I left.
^Wow, that sounds terrible. No wonder you're looking for someone else to orbit.

s: ^Thank you for being so kind to me.

c-0: ^I should be thanking you. You were kind to me first.
c-1: ^I was wondering when you would ask that...
^You watch as Europa races towards you and Jupiter. The other moons follow.
^You better not bring them in without talking with us!
^Especially now that I have to check them for humans!
^Looks like there's going to be a group discussion first. I'll let you know a bit later, okay?

silent: ^For a moment, neither of you say anything. The silence is nice, a period of tranquility without the sound of 96 moons all fighting for attention.
^Alright hun, our turn for the private conversation.
^We've got to talk with Jupie about getting you in our circle!
^And about getting you checked for humans. You better not have any!
^Moon, I know you're still looking for an orbit. I'll talk with the others and get back to you, okay?
main: ^Thanks for hanging out. It was really nice.

JupiterFourth: ^Hi... you wanted to talk to me again?
^Well, I had a chat with the other moons, and... we'd like you to join us.
^Hun, you're an absolute delight. You deserve someone way better than Earth.
^I would love to join you in orbit.
^Yay! We're glad to have you around!
^As long as you don't get in my way. And you don't bring humans here. And--
^Moon, I promise to treat you better than Earth ever could. You'll never feel alone with us.
^Hey, wait a minute. We can't just call you Moon! We're ALL moons!
^Oh, you're right! I never had a name with Earth... hmm...
^And so, Luna joined Jupiter in their orbit. And though the moons still frequently bickered, Jupiter was much happier. And Luna was loved.
^Oh, Jupiter... you mean the world to me.
